---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout pageTitle="About — Jirka Sindelar" description="About Jirka Sindelar — software engineer, builder, learner.">

  <!-- Intro: photo + opener, side by side on desktop -->
  <section class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-6 sm:gap-8 items-start">
    <img
      src="/jirka-photo.png"
      alt="Jirka Sindelar"
      class="w-48 h-48 sm:w-56 sm:h-56 rounded-xl object-cover shrink-0"
    />
    <div>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold">Jirka Sindelar</h1>
      <p class="mt-3 text-lg text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300">
        <!-- WRITE: 2-3 sentences, meetup energy opener.
             Think: what would you say in the first 30 seconds after someone asks
             "so what do you do?" at a meetup. Not a job title — the energy.
             e.g. "Deep in flow, building stuff, exploring new ideas emerging in software."
             Your original line above is a great start — expand it slightly. -->
        Deep in flow, building stuff, exploring new ideas emerging in software.
        Lately, I’ve been digging into Open Banking and building an agentic app.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The arc: your story, not your resume -->
  <section class="mt-10 space-y-4 text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">The story</h2>
    <!-- WRITE: 2-3 paragraphs in your voice. The arc:
         - Prague banking tech, Java backend, the people who inspired you
         - What clicked — the moment you wanted more than backend
         - Melbourne, the shift to full-stack, building end-to-end
         - What you're chasing now (agentic design, product thinking, the full SDLC)
         Keep it conversational — "look man, this is what happened" energy. -->
    <p>
      It was great years in Prague’s banking technology, 
      working on Java backends and surrounded by brilliant people,
      who developed staff around the world. So, I recall my quote of my grandpa's shop foreman:
      “Are you a panel beater? Not yet. Maybe one day. For now, you’re steam rising off a pile of panel beater's shit.”
      Well, I moved to Melbourne, got sparked to full-stack, 
      product creation, diving into agentic design.
    </p>
    <p>
      Based in Melbourne.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- What I'm into now -->
  <section class="mt-10 space-y-4 text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">What I'm into now</h2>
    <!-- WRITE: What's on your desk right now. Specific projects, specific obsessions.
         An engineer reading this should think "oh, I want to talk to him about X."
         e.g. agentic design, building this site end-to-end, the agent marketplace idea,
         learning React through Astro islands, etc. -->
    <p>
      I build Mortgage readiness copilot which is B2B2C app based on Open banking and agentic design.
      
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- What I'm open to -->
  <section class="mt-10 space-y-4 text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">What I'm open to</h2>
    <!-- WRITE: Specific enough that someone can self-qualify.
         Not "interesting projects" — what KIND of projects? - I don't know
    -->
    <p>
      If you're into Open Banking, agentic design, or product development, let's chat!
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- Outside of code -->
  <section class="mt-10 space-y-4 text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Outside of code</h2>
    <p>
      Improv, history, philosophy, volunteering, and nature.
    </p>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>
